The '''2007 Washington State Cougars football team''' represented [[Washington State University]] in the [[college football]] [[2007 NCAA Division I-BS football season|season of 2007-2008]]. The team was led by fifth-year head coach [[Bill Doba]] and played its home games at [[Martin Stadium]] in [[Pullman, Washington|Pullman]], [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington]].
The 2007 [[Apple Cup]] was played a week later than normal to allow for both [[Washington Huskies football|Washington]] and Washington State to have a bye, as neither had one in 2006. This marked the first time the Apple Cup has been played after [[Thanksgiving]] since 1978.<ref>[http://wsucougars.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/011907aaa.html Cougars Finalize 2007 Schedule; Apple Cup Played Thanksgiving Weekend :: Apple Cup to be played after Thanksgiving for first time since 1978 season<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
Three days after leading the Cougars to a 42-35 victory in the Apple Cup, head coach [[Bill Doba]] was fired on November 26.<ref>[http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/sports/2004036104_webdobafired26.html Cougars | WSU fires head coach Doba | Seattle Times Newspaper<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Doba posted a 30-29 record during his 5 seasons as head coach; and led the Cougars to only 1 bowl game, a 28-20 victory over [[Texas Longhorns football|Texas]] in the [[2003 Holiday Bowl]] in his first season.
